{"id":237,"date":"2008-08-28T20:44:03","date_gmt":"2008-08-28T18:44:03","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/?page_id=237"},"modified":"2008-09-01T13:07:46","modified_gmt":"2008-09-01T11:07:46","slug":"inventive_ability","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/learning\/graphology_course\/methodically_uneven\/inventive_ability","title":{"rendered":"Inventive ability in the Morettian graphology"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Intuition, as described above, operates through intelligence skills in:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>precise observation of every small but significant variation occurring in the environment;<\/li>\n<li>variations assembling in order to identify relevant patterns present in the specific context which could be useful for interpretation or adaptation.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Such ability is based on a simple premise: all life manifestations, though linked to uniqueness and consequently to differentiation (this is true both if we are talking about two raindrops and about two apparently very similar life events) cannot be understood separately, but receive their specific meaning from their context. Moreover, apparently different events can fall under the very same interpretation criteria.<\/p>\n<p>Therefore, the personality skill to connect with its own creative movement requires the ability to express both the above mentioned movements inside itself: that is, to recognize the endless variations belonging to life itself\u00a0 by entering into resonance with them, as a starting point to get subsequently to grasp the structures, laws, great interpretative principles leading life, as in the world, though facing an impressive manifestation of uniqueness with a perfectly defined identity\u00a0 it is also present an equally impressive evidence of harmonic consistency of the different facets of uniqueness.<\/p>\n<p>Such an intuitive understanding of the laws connected with creativity led Moretti to describe the graphological sign \u201cMethodically Uneven\u201d as a measure of the personality originality, which needs &#8211; as prerequisites &#8211; both the following characteristics:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>the uninterrupted variation of the writing, as a measure of the personality skill to connect with the uniqueness\u00a0 present inside life itself;<\/li>\n<li>the notion of rhythm, here defined as \u201cmethod\u201d, as a measure of the personality skill to connect and understand variations identifying the underlying reference frames.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<ul>\n<li>Fig. 1 \u2013  Newton handwriting, showing in a high degree both prerequisite, unevenness and method in graphic variation.<br \/><a href=\"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/wp-content\/uploads\/handwriting069.jpg\" title=\"Handwriting: Isaac Newton\"><img src=\"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/wp-content\/uploads\/handwriting069.thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"Handwriting: Isaac Newton\" \/><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Somehow, as uniqueness belongs to life, no handwriting can be without unevenness, because it cannot exist &#8211; in life, but above all, in man and woman &#8211; something devoid of uniqueness, therefore of originality; at the same time, it is very difficult to imagine a total lack of method, that is, of the ability to process simple data and organize them according to frames made for\u00a0 learning and understanding the environment: elsewhere, we would obtain a totally split personality.<\/p>\n<p>The following graphological and psychological features are to be evaluated: the level of variation capacity, its\u00a0 diffusion and methodicity, which produce the sign \u201cMethodically Uneven\u201d and \u201cRandomly Uneven\u201d.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fig. 2 \u2013 Example of methodic but not widespread variation (the sign Methodically Uneven shows sometimes)<br \/>\n<a href=\"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/wp-content\/uploads\/handwriting070.jpg\" title=\"Handwriting: Methodically Uneven\"><img src=\"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/wp-content\/uploads\/handwriting070.thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"Handwriting: Methodically Uneven\" \/><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Fig. 3 \u2013 Example of widespread but not methodical variation (Randomly Uneven).<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<a href=\"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/wp-content\/uploads\/handwriting071.jpg\" title=\"Handwriting: IRandomly Uneven\"><img src=\"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/wp-content\/uploads\/handwriting071.thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"Handwriting: Randomly Uneven\" \/><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Whenever such unevenness is very slight &#8211; to the point of giving an impression of variationless writing &#8211; here we find a kind of intelligence not original but inclined to technique (graphological sign \u201cEven\u201d), that is to an impersonal use of \u201cpassed on\u201d rules, without the screening of the creative interpretations\u00a0 performed by the Ego, a situation that may sometimes be of advantage.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fig. 4 \u2013 Handwriting inclined to be Even (size homogeneity is predominant)<br \/>\n<a href=\"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/wp-content\/uploads\/handwriting072.jpg\" title=\"Handwriting: Even\"><img src=\"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/wp-content\/uploads\/handwriting072.thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"Handwriting: Even\" \/><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Intuition, as described above, operates through intelligence skills in: precise observation of every small but significant variation occurring in the environment; variations assembling in order to identify relevant patterns present in the specific context which could be useful for interpretation or adaptation. Such ability is based on a simple premise: all life manifestations, though linked [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":227,"menu_order":2,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/237"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.graphology.it\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/